<section class="panel">
    <h2>SSE Control Events</h2>
    <p>Named SSE events do not swap HTML directly in HTMX 2. Instead they dispatch <code>sse:&lt;event&gt;</code> so ordinary HTMX requests can react.</p>
    <div class="demo-note" role="note">
        <strong>How To Test:</strong> load this route and wait. Four control-event cards should upgrade one-by-one after <code>stale</code>, <code>rate-limited</code>, <code>reset</code>, and <code>unauthorized</code> fire, then the connection should stop after the blank-data <code>done</code> event.
    </div>
</section>

<section class="sse-demo-grid">
    <section class="panel">
        <h3>Named Event Listeners</h3>
        <p class="demo-caption">Each card listens with <code>hx-trigger="sse:&lt;event&gt;"</code> and fetches its replacement through the normal HTMX request pipeline.</p>

        <section
            id="sse-control-shell"
            class="sse-live-shell"
            hx-ext="sse"
            sse-connect="/demos/sse/control-events/stream"
            sse-close="@HrzSseEventNames.Done">
            <div id="sse-control-grid" class="activity-feed sse-live-feed" aria-live="polite">
                <SseControlEventPanel
                    Id="sse-control-stale"
                    EventName="@HrzSseEventNames.Stale"
                    Title="Waiting for stale"
                    Detail="No stale signal has been dispatched yet."
                    Tone="neutral" />
                <SseControlEventPanel
                    Id="sse-control-rate-limited"
                    EventName="@HrzSseEventNames.RateLimited"
                    Title="Waiting for rate-limited"
                    Detail="No reconnect throttling signal has been dispatched yet."
                    Tone="neutral" />
                <SseControlEventPanel
                    Id="sse-control-reset"
                    EventName="@HrzSseEventNames.Reset"
                    Title="Waiting for reset"
                    Detail="No reset signal has been dispatched yet."
                    Tone="neutral" />
                <SseControlEventPanel
                    Id="sse-control-unauthorized"
                    EventName="@HrzSseEventNames.Unauthorized"
                    Title="Waiting for unauthorized"
                    Detail="No authorization failure signal has been dispatched yet."
                    Tone="neutral" />
            </div>
        </section>
    </section>

    <section class="panel sse-sidecar-panel">
        <h3>Contract</h3>
        <p class="demo-caption">The SSE response only emits named control events. The visible cards update because HTMX converts those named events into regular fragment requests.</p>

        <SseDemoStatusCard
            Label="transport"
            Title="Signal, then fetch"
            Detail="The stream delivers only control signals here. HyperRazor still uses ordinary fragment rendering for the replacement HTML."
            Tone="resume" />

        <p class="demo-caption mb-0">
            Need the unnamed HTML swap path too?
            <a href="/demos/sse">Open SSE basics.</a>
        </p>
    </section>
</section>
